      "- A10 SSRF",
      "",
      "Load context first with `read_context { \"module\": \"${1}\" }`, then flag any findings with severity and remediation.",
      "${0}"
    ],
    "description": "OWASP-structured security review"
  },

  "ContextForge: Generate docs": {
    "prefix": "cf-docs",
    "body": [
      "Generate documentation for **${1:function/class/module}**.",
      "",
      "Load its signature with `search_signatures { \"query\": \"${1}\" }`, then produce:",
      "- Summary description (2–3 sentences)",
      "- Parameter table (name, type, description)",
      "- Return value description",
      "- Usage example",
      "${0}"
    ],
    "description": "Generate documentation from signatures"
  },

  "ContextForge: Explain codebase": {
    "prefix": "cf-explain",
    "body": [
      "Explain how **${1:module/system/flow}** works to someone who is new to this codebase.",
      "",
      "1. Load context with `read_context { \"module\": \"${1}\" }`",
      "2. Describe the key components and their responsibilities",
      "3. Walk through the most important code path",
      "4. Highlight any non-obvious design decisions",
      "${0}"
    ],
    "description": "Explain a part of the codebase to a newcomer"
  },

  "ContextForge: Migration guide": {
    "prefix": "cf-migrate",
    "body": [
      "I need to migrate **${1:library/pattern/API}** from `${2:old version/approach}` to `${3:new version/approach}`.",
      "",
      "1. Load context with `read_context` to find all call sites",
      "2. List every file that needs updating",
      "3. Provide a migration checklist with concrete code changes for each pattern",
      "${0}"
    ],
    "description": "Context-aware migration guide for library or API changes"
  },

  "ContextForge: End session": {
    "prefix": "cf-end",
    "body": [
      "Create a final session checkpoint using `create_checkpoint { \"note\": \"${1:session summary}\" }`.",
      "",
      "Then provide a handoff note covering:",
      "- **Completed:** What was implemented or fixed",
      "- **In progress:** Work partially done with current status",
      "- **Next steps:** Recommended tasks for the next session",
      "- **Decisions made:** Any significant choices or trade-offs",
      "${0}"
